<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--Diamonds     04-21 0163</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Diamonds,0169</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Jewelry Dealer Bought Largest Diamond Ever Sold At Auction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A London jewelry dealer was identified as the
person who paid $9.13 million for the largest diamond ever to be
sold at auction, a Sotheby's spokeswoman said.
   Laurence Graff purchased the 85.91-carat, pear-shaped diamond by
telephone during Tuesday's auction, spokeswoman Jennifer Brown said
Wednesday.
   The sale set a record for any gem sold at auction, she said.
   The diamond, which was perfectly cut and flawless, was part of
an auction that brought $36 million, a record for a jewelry sale in
the United States.
   The auction included gems belonging to the late Clare Boothe
Luce, a former congresswoman and ambassador to Italy.
   Also Wednesday, Christie's announced the sale of a 52.59 carat
diamond ring for $7.8 million, the highest price ever paid per
carat at auction, said spokeswoman Lily Zimmerman.
   She said $132,000 was paid per carat by a private Saudi Arabian
collector bidding by telephone.
</TEXT>
