<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--AuschwitzConvent     04-21 0160</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Auschwitz Convent,0163</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rabbi Says Convent at Auschwitz Being Renovated</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Roman Catholic Carmelite convent on the grounds
of Auschwitz is being renovated, French Rabbi Daniel Fahri said
after visiting the World War II Nazi death camp in Poland.
   Jews by the hundreds of thousands died in Auschwitz's gas
chambers.
   The international Jewish community opposed plans to establish a
convent there and an agreement was signed Feb. 22 in Geneva to move
the convent to a nearby location within two years.
   Fahri said on Wednesday, ``During a pilgrimage I organized at
Auschwitz on April 17, I could see that the building housing the
convent had been completely sandblasted, both inside and outside.
   ``The facade and the roofing of the convent have been completely
redone. Last year, the building was simply falling apart.''
   He said a deputy archbishop at Krakow, Poland, seemed
``embarrassed'' when asked about the renovations and ``ended up by
saying he didn't know anything.''
</TEXT>
