<1ST_LINE>r w BC-HouseImmigrationRollCall 3Takes   04-21 0481</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-House Immigration Roll Call, 3 Takes,480</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 213-201 roll call Wednesday by
which the House agreed to extend the amnesty application deadline
for illegal aliens from May 4 to Nov. 30.
   A ``yes'' vote is a vote to extend the deadline.
   Voting yes were 181 Democrats and 32 Republicans.
   Voting no were 64 Democrats and 137 Republicans.
   x denotes those not voting.
   Present denotes those who voted they were ``present'' at the
time of the vote but did not vote ``yes'' or ``no'' on the issue.
   There are three vacancies in the 435-member House.
</TEXT>
