<HEAD>Dollar Higher, Stocks Lower In Tokyo Morning Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar finished higher Thursday against the
Japanese yen in Tokyo, while stock prices lost slightly.
   The dollar ended the day at 124.30 yen, up 0.40 yen from its
close of 123.90 yen Wednesday. It had opened the day at 124.27 yen
and fluctuated in narrow range of 124.20 yen to 124.36 yen.
   ``The dollar is somewhat strengthened following overnight
dollar-purchasings in overseas markets and the selling of European
currencies,'' said an exchange dealer at a major commercial bank in
Tokyo.
   The dealer, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said a U.S.
Labor Department report Wednesday that American consumer prices
jumped 0.5 percent during March had no major impact on the currency
market.
   ``The worsening figures were what many expected,'' the dealer
said.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average,
a 207.09-point winner Wednesday, shed a light 35.93 points, or 0.13
percent, closing the day at 26,828.16.
   ``The third consecutive setback on Wall Street overnight
prompted a sense of uncertainty over market propects among
investors,'' said an official of a major securities firm, speaking
on condition of anonymity.
   He said trading was thin as institutional investors stayed out
of the market.
</TEXT>
