<FILEID>AP-NR-04-21-88 0555EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a PM-CrimeFighter     04-21 0347</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Crime Fighter,0358</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Elderly Alderwoman Helps Nab Shooting Suspect</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ELIZABETH SHOGREN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 70-year-old alderwoman credited with helping
catch a shooting suspect says she has been patrolling her
crime-ridden, economically depressed ward since she was assigned a
bodyguard earlier this year.
   Before the bodyguard, Anna Langford said, she jumped into the
middle of sticky situations on her own.
   ``I have a desire to see my ward free of crime, and if they know
somebody out there is watching them and working with the police, it
may be a deterrent,'' Ms. Langford said Wednesday.
   Ms. Langford said she and her bodyguard, police officer Eddie
McCann, decided to end an evening of cruising for crime Tuesday
when they heard over a police scanner that someone had been shot.
   When they arrived at the scene, the victim _ who had been shot
four times in a squabble over a girlfriend _ already had been taken
to the hospital, Ms. Langford said.
   The suspect had fled, but a few women were standing around
``screaming and crying,'' McCann said.
   ``She (Ms. Langford) was the one who calmed the women down in
order for us to get a description of the offender and the direction
of his flight,'' McCann said.
   Ms. Langford also persuaded the women to tell police the name
and address of the suspect, McCann said.
   McCann said he and a detective found the suspect, Kevin Smith,
in a closet of the apartment the women had directed them to. Smith
was arrested and has been charged with attempted murder, police
said.
   ``If the alderwoman hadn't been on the scene, the offender could
very well still be at large,'' McCann said.
   ``Intervening in street incidents ... is something I've always
done,'' said Ms. Langford, a retired criminal lawyer.
   Ms. Langford said she was assigned a bodyguard because of recent
threats on her life. ``But we've turned out to be a crime fighting
team. He and I are just naturally into things.''
   The 19-year-old shooting victim was in fair condition today,
Cook County Hospital officials said.
</TEXT>
