<2ND_LINE>PM-Toy Repair,140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Safety Repair Kit Offered for Speed Wheels</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A repair kit is being offered for the Schaper
``Speed Wheels'' ride-on toy to prevent children's fingers from
becoming trapped between the pedal bar and the toy's body, the
Consumer Product Safety Commission announced today.
   About 25,000 of the toys were sold without finger guards in
1986, and the repair kit supplies those guards. Eight incidents of
cuts or severed fingertips have been reported, the commission said.
   Involved is the Schaper Speed Wheels toy, model number 61106.
   The repair kits are available by writing Speed Wheels Corrective
Action Program, Tyco Toys Inc., 540 Glen Avenue., Moorestown, N.J.,
08057, or by calling 1-800-257-7728.
   Speed Wheels was designed and sold by Schaper Manufacturing Co.
of Minneapolis, but Tyco has since purchased that firm.
   Individuals needing more information can contact the safety
commission at 1-800-638-2772.
</TEXT>
