<HEAD>Bright & Brief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOISE, Idaho (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The names ``Owyhee View'' and ``Southern
Desert'' were nice, but they just didn't seem to project the right
image.
   Idaho Maximum Security Prison, however, was a perfect fit.
   ``It connotes exactly what kind of place it is,'' said L. James
Koutnik, a member of the Idaho Board of Correction. ``It's not a
flower garden or a country club. It's a maximum-security prison.''
   Tim McNeese, assistant corrections director, said the department
has received suggestions for a name including Owyhee View Prison to
Southern Desert Correctional Facility. The prison is being built in
the high desert from which the Owyhee Mountains are visible.
   Board members said some states name their prisons after people.
To which Corrections Director Al Murphy said, ``I don't want to
hear `Happy Al's Correctional Facility.''
   The vote Wednesday was unanimous for Idaho Maximum Security
Prison.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>BRIDGEPORT, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Avoiding alcohol after the prom could be
beneficial _ and not just for the obvious reasons.
   Students who attend an after-prom party Saturday night will have
a chance to win a 1976 Mercury Montego worth at least $500.
   Organizers said the event is designed to offer students an
alternative to customary parties with alcohol.
   Students who wear formal attire to the party, arrive within 30
minutes of the end of the prom and stay until the end of the
festivities will be eligible to win the car. Special drawings also
are planned for a VCR and dinner for two.
   Co-chair Barbara Nelson said the car has 140,000 miles on it,
but a mechanic has checked it and it appears to be in good shape.
   ``A bunch of us mothers are going to wax it. We think it's going
to be OK,'' she said.
</TEXT>
