<HEAD>Former Director of Stratford Theater Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STRATFORD, Ontario (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Jean Gascon, the French-Canadian actor
and director who served as artistic director of the Stratford
Festival in Ontario from 1969 to 1974, has died at the age of 67.
   Gascon fell ill this month while directing a production of ``My
Fair Lady'' for the 1988 Stratford Festival. He died of heart
failure Wednesday night.
   A former director of theater at the National Arts Center in
Ottawa, Gascon was born and raised in Montreal, the sixth of 14
children. He studied in France and began his acting career at
Stratford in 1956.
