<HEAD>Police Arrest 94-year-old `Madam'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PESCARA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police who raided a bordello in this
coastal city on the Adriatic said they arrested a 94-year-old woman
and charged her with running the operation.
   Maria Enrica Sparvieri was arrested Wednesday on charges of
arranging for illicit sexual encounters and released on her own
recognizance.
   ``She's very sprightly; she had to be to run such a business,''
said the policeman, who spoke on condition of anonymity.
   The policeman said about a half dozen women worked at the
bordello, but no one else was arrested in the raid.
