<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A grand jury indicted 10 men Thursday in
an alleged kidnapping and gang rape March 26 of a young woman who
told police that bystanders at a cockfight ignored her cries and
joined in the attack.
   ``We got everything we wanted,'' Duvall County Assistant
District Attorney Rudy Gutierrez said in announcing the indictments.
   The 10 were arrested within days of the alleged attack that
shocked this southern Texas town of 5,000, where many residents are
related.
   The 19-year-old woman, a mother of two, told authorities she was
abducted while walking home from a relative's house and gang raped
over four hours.
   She said the attack began at a ranch north of town where a
cockfight was being held. She said her attackers urged men at the
cockfight to join in, and some did, despite her pleas for help.
   Some of the defendants, who were charged with offenses including
sexual assault and kidnapping, had charged she was a willing
participant.
   Richard Yaegear, a family friend, said the woman, her husband
and children are in a secret location in Corpus Christi because
they had been threatened.
   ``They have to get out of San Diego,'' said Yaeger. ``They'll
never be able to come back here. These people here are acting like
(the victim and her family) are in the wrong.''
   Those testifying before the grand jury Thursday included a
12-year-old boy who claimed to have seen part of the attack,
Guttierez said.
   Officials also are investigating a report that a 14-year-old boy
was involved in the sexual attack, said County Attorney Abelardo
Garza.
