<1ST_LINE>r a AM-OriolesNewspage     04-21 0142</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Orioles Newspage,0145</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Orioles Set A Losing Record</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILWAUKEE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Baltimore Orioles set a major league record
Wednesdasy night for the longest season-opening losing streak _ 14
games.
   The hapless Orioles fell to the Milwaukee Brewers 8-6 as Jim
Gantner's bases-loaded single sparked a four-run fifth inning.
Baltimore had led 5-3 in the fifth inning in its highest-scoring
game of the season.
   Baltimore, in losing its first 14 games of the season, overtook
both the 1904 Washington Senators and the 1920 Detroit Tigers, who
lost their first 13 games.
   The longest major-league losing streak at any time during a
season is 23 games, set in 1961 by the Philadelphia Phillies. The
Orioles' 14th straight loss tied the team record for consecutive
losses, set in 1954.
   A crowd of 7,284 watched on a windy night with temperatures in
the 40s.
</TEXT>
