<HEAD>Borden Loses Another Court Battle Over Lemon Juice</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: ReaLemon in 2nd graf is CQ</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   U.S. food giant Borden Inc. lost another round
Thursday in its court battle to squeeze into the British lemon
juice market.
   The Court of Appeal dismissed Borden's appeal against last
year's High Court ruling preventing the company from selling
ReaLemon on the grounds consumers would confuse it with Jif, a
popular British product manufactured by Reckitt and Colman.
   Both products contain lemon juice in plastic lemon-shaped
squeeze containers.
   Reckitt and Colman has fought off several rival products since
introducing Jif in 1957 and Lord Justice Slade said it had
established an exclusive right to the particular ``get-up'' of the
product.
