<HEAD>Mitsubishi Motors To Recall 38,661 Cars</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mitsubishi Motors Co. of Japan has notified the
Transport Ministry it will recall 38,661 automobiles because of a
defective pinion in steering equipment, the ministry said.
   A ministry official, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said
Thursday the cars included six models: Mirage, Lancer Fiore, Mirage
Wagon, Lancer Wagon, Mirage Van and Lancer Van. The vehicles were
produced between June 1, 1984 and Oct. 15, 1985.
   Of the total to be recalled, 5,476 cars had been exported, the
official said. He said 1,702 cars were exported to Cyprus, 763 to
Sri Lanka, 638 to Singapore and the rest to other Asian nations.
None of the cars were exported to the United States or Europe.
