<HEAD>Production Goes Up This Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
242,689 cars and trucks this week, down from last week's 245,290,
Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   Automakers produced 203,534 cars and trucks during the same week
a year ago. They were were scheduled to make 155,946 cars this
week, compared with 158,565 a week ago and 138,895 in the same week
in 1987.
   Truck production for the week was scheduled at 86,743, compared
with last week's 86,725 and last year's 64,639.
   Canadian automakers were to build 27,040 cars this week,
compared with 24,265 last week and 17,532 in the same week last
year. Canadian truck production was scheduled at 20,785, compared
with 20,434 last week and 18,532 in the same week last year.
