<1ST_LINE>u f PM-WallStreetClosing     04-21 0117</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street Closing,0127</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A sudden afternoon downdraft wiped out an early
gain in the stock market today, leaving prices little changed from
Wednesday.
   Analysts said swings in prices of stock-index futures prompted
professionals engaged in program trading to sell the futures and
buy individual stocks in the early going.
   At midafternoon, they said, the balance abruptly reversed and
selling programs hit the stock market.
   Brokers said the effect was especially pronounced because many
other investors have been shying away from the stock market lately,
and thus contributing to its potential volatility.
   They noted that many stocks haven't responded much so far to
generally strong earnings reports for the first quarter.
</TEXT>
