<1ST_LINE>u f AM-Earns-Computer     04-21 0348</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Earns-Computer,0361</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Compaq Earnings Soar 132 Percent; TI Sinks; Data General Earns
Profit</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Compaq Computer Corp.'s profit rose 132 percent and its revenue
rose 108 percent in the latest quarter, the mushrooming maker of
personal computers said Thursday.
   Among other technology companies, semiconductor maker Texas
Instruments Inc. of Dallas said its profit fell 4.9 percent and
minicomputer maker Data General Corp. of Westboro, Mass., said it
made a profit in contrast to a year-earlier loss.
   Texas Instruments announced separately that Jerry R. Junkins
will take on the title of chairman upon the retirement of Mark
Shepherd Jr., which was previously announced. Junkins is already
president and chief executive.
   Compaq, which reached the Fortune 500 and the $1 billion annual
sales mark faster than any other company, continued to skyrocket in
the first quarter.
   The Houston-based company attributed the gains to international
market growth, a strong brand image and sales of its
top-of-the-line products, including the Deskpro 386-20.
   Compaq's profit rose to $47 million, or $1.21 a share, from $20
million, or 56 cents a share, a year earlier. Revenue rose to $439
million from $211 million.
   Texas Instruments, which makes computer chips, defense
electronics and other products, said its profit fell to $85.5
million, or 95 cents a share, from $89.9 million, or $1.12 a share,
a year earlier. Revenue rose 15.4 percent to $1.47 billion from
$1.27 billion.
   Data General said net income for its second fiscal quarter
totaled $17.2 million, or 57 cents a share, a reversal from a $42.6
million loss in the same period last year. The computer maker
reported revenues of $349.7 million, a 10.9 percent increase over
last year's $315.2 million.
   The company attributed part of the rise to the $5.9 million sale
of a company facility in Austin, Texas, during the quarter.
   For the six-month period ending March 26, Data General reported
net income of $29.6 million, or $1.01 a share, compared with a net
loss of $39.3 million in the same period a year earlier. Revenue
rose 10.2 percent to $692.5 million from $628.5 million.
</TEXT>
